cs.SE, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CY

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new approach for bug triage, which is a common task in software engineering.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the paper uses text classification techniques to classify bug reports.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses a combination of naive Bayes classifier and expectation-maximization for semi-supervised learning.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is relevant as the paper deals with natural language processing of bug reports.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the impact of the proposed approach on software development and the role of developers in bug triage.
